      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesnt feel like just bureaucracy though. every time i try to explain the fractal scaling component, the responses i get are so patronizing, like they're trying to steer me back to the standard model. it's like there's a specific protocol to keep people from looking too closely at the Planck-density threshold. if i can just show them how the non-linear geometry resolves the singularity issue, they have to listen, right? or is there a reason why certain breakthroughs just... get buried?",
